<tr id="L20"><td><a href="#L20">20</a></td><td>JANEWAY:  I suppose I did.</td></tr>

<tr id="L21"><td><a href="#L21">21</a></td><td>TORRES:  That's what my mother used to call me.</td></tr>

<tr id="L22"><td><a href="#L22">22</a></td><td>JANEWAY:  Well then, I'm in good company.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Torres' quarters</td></tr>
<tr id="L23"><td><a href="#L23">23</a></td><td>TORRES:  Come in.</td></tr>

<tr id="L24"><td><a href="#L24">24</a></td><td>CHAKOTAY:  Feeling better?</td></tr>

<tr id="L25"><td><a href="#L25">25</a></td><td>TORRES:  I've felt worse.</td></tr>

<tr id="L26"><td><a href="#L26">26</a></td><td>CHAKOTAY:  I found something you might be interested in. It's what my ancestors called a monkey wrench. It was lodged in your port nacelle.</td></tr>

<tr id="L27"><td><a href="#L27">27</a></td><td>TORRES:  How did it get there?</td></tr>

<tr id="L28"><td><a href="#L28">28</a></td><td>CHAKOTAY:  Judging by your sensor logs, it looks like you ran into it after your deflector field collapsed, but the big question is, how did it get in this quadrant?</td></tr>

<tr id="L29"><td><a href="#L29">29</a></td><td>TORRES:  What do you mean? (She takes the piece of metal from Chakotay, and sees the insignia on it. A circle with one big elongated diamond and two small curved triangles sticking out from it.)</td></tr>

<tr id="L30"><td><a href="#L30">30</a></td><td>TORRES:  What? It's Klingon!</td></tr>

<tr id="L31"><td><a href="#L31">31</a></td><td>CHAKOTAY:  And it's old. That's about all we know. Looks like the Klingons beat Starfleet to the Delta Quadrant by a few hundred years. You may be holding the most important archaeological find in Klingon history.</td></tr>

<tr id="L32"><td><a href="#L32">32</a></td><td>TORRES:  Remind me to plant a flag on behalf of the Empire. You know, the simplest explanation is that the Borg assimilated a Bird of Prey somewhere in the Alpha Quadrant and they blew it out an airlock on their way home.</td></tr>

<tr id="L33"><td><a href="#L33">33</a></td><td>CHAKOTAY:  Maybe so. In any case, it makes a nice souvenir.</td></tr>

<tr id="L34"><td><a href="#L34">34</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Chakotay leaves it with her. Torres puts it down on a table and goes to the replicator. When she turns back, blood is pouring from the insignia. Then she hears a multitude of voices, until it all vanishes again.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Engineering</td></tr>
<tr id="L35"><td><a href="#L35">35</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: The metal is on a stand.</td></tr>

<tr id="L36"><td><a href="#L36">36</a></td><td>TORRES:  Harry, it bled. Ut screamed. There's got to be some explanation.</td></tr>

<tr id="L37"><td><a href="#L37">37</a></td><td>KIM:  Hey, I've got one for you. You hit your head harder than you thought.</td></tr>

<tr id="L38"><td><a href="#L38">38</a></td><td>TORRES:  I wasn't hallucinating. Now run a submolecular scan.</td></tr>

<tr id="L39"><td><a href="#L39">39</a></td><td>KIM:  How many more scans are we going to run? There's nothing there. No fluid or vapour residue.</td></tr>

<tr id="L40"><td><a href="#L40">40</a></td><td>TORRES:  We may find some irregularities at the atomic level.</td></tr>

<tr id="L41"><td><a href="#L41">41</a></td><td>KIM:  It's a hunk of metal. What you heard may have had nothing to do with this artefact. Maybe the comm. system picked up some stray signal from a pulsar. I don't know.</td></tr>

<tr id="L42"><td><a href="#L42">42</a></td><td>TORRES:  A pulsar that speaks Klingon?</td></tr>

<tr id="L43"><td><a href="#L43">43</a></td><td>KIM:  Okay, B'Elanna, there probably is some explanation for what happened. But it's oh three hundred hours. I'm tired, you're tired. Let's just stick this thing in a containment field and deal with it in the morning.</td></tr>

<tr id="L44"><td><a href="#L44">44</a></td><td>NEELIX:  Ah! Just the Daughter of the Empire I've been looking for. I wanted to be the first to congratulate you on your discovery of the Klingon artefact.</td></tr>

<tr id="L45"><td><a href="#L45">45</a></td><td>TORRES:  Neelix, I ran into it with a shuttle.</td></tr>

<tr id="L46"><td><a href="#L46">46</a></td><td>NEELIX:  Some of the greatest discoveries in Klingon history were accidents. When Sarpek the Fearless unearthed the Knife of Kirom he was searching for his lost targ. Isn't that amazing? I've been doing some research.</td></tr>

<tr id="L47"><td><a href="#L47">47</a></td><td>TORRES:  Why?</td></tr>

<tr id="L48"><td><a href="#L48">48</a></td><td>NEELIX:  Well, I'm planning a celebration. This must be the treasure.</td></tr>

<tr id="L49"><td><a href="#L49">49</a></td><td>TORRES:  Neelix, look, I appreciate your enthusiasm, but since I'm the only Klingon on board, there's really no point in throwing a party.</td></tr>

<tr id="L50"><td><a href="#L50">50</a></td><td>NEELIX:  Oh, nonsense. This artefact isn't just a testament to Klingon spirit. It's a piece of the Alpha Quadrant. A symbol of Voyager's home. And that's just as worthy of celebration and song as finding some old knife.</td></tr>

<tr id="L51"><td><a href="#L51">51</a></td><td>KIM:  The man's got a point.</td></tr>

<tr id="L52"><td><a href="#L52">52</a></td><td>NEELIX:  And besides, I've already replicated five barrels of bloodwine. I'm not going to let them go to waste. Festivities begin at nineteen hundred hours. Oh, er, I almost forgot. As guest of honour, you're going to be expected to say a few words on behalf of your people.</td></tr>

<tr id="L53"><td><a href="#L53">53</a></td><td>KIM:  It sounds like you've got a big day ahead of you. You should probably get some rest.</td></tr>

<tr id="L54"><td><a href="#L54">54</a></td><td>TORRES:  All right, all right, let's call it a night.</td></tr>

<tr id="L55"><td><a href="#L55">55</a></td><td>KIM:  Thank you.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Tuvok's quarters</td></tr>
<tr id="L56"><td><a href="#L56">56</a></td><td>TUVOK:  Do not underestimate the power of the mind. The artefact was a catalyst for your already active imagination. It served as an unwelcome reminder of your ancestry. The self-loathing you experience when you look in the mirror and see a Klingon.</td></tr>

<tr id="L57"><td><a href="#L57">57</a></td><td>TORRES:  Who said anything about self-loathing?</td></tr>

<tr id="L58"><td><a href="#L58">58</a></td><td>TUVOK:  You despise being Klingon. It's no secret. What you experienced in your quarters was a subconscious manifestation of that hatred. The blood in your veins, the voices of your ancestors, all symbols of your Klingon heritage.</td></tr>

<tr id="L59"><td><a href="#L59">59</a></td><td>TORRES:  And when the blood disappeared that was, what, me trying to vaporise that part of myself?</td></tr>

<tr id="L60"><td><a href="#L60">60</a></td><td>TUVOK:  Yes, but the essence of who you are, the artefact itself, remained.</td></tr>

<tr id="L61"><td><a href="#L61">61</a></td><td>TORRES:  And the moral of the story is?</td></tr>

<tr id="L62"><td><a href="#L62">62</a></td><td>TUVOK:  Quite simple. That despite your efforts to become something else, whether it be Starfleet or Maquis, your Klingon nature continues to assert itself.</td></tr>

<tr id="L63"><td><a href="#L63">63</a></td><td>TORRES:  That's an intriguing theory.</td></tr>

<tr id="L64"><td><a href="#L64">64</a></td><td>TUVOK:  Perhaps we should forego your meditation in favour of a different exercise.</td></tr>

<tr id="L65"><td><a href="#L65">65</a></td><td>TORRES:  Fine by me. (Tuvok fetches a bat'leth.)</td></tr>

<tr id="L66"><td><a href="#L66">66</a></td><td>TORRES:  This should be interesting.</td></tr>

<tr id="L67"><td><a href="#L67">67</a></td><td>TUVOK:  Feel the weight of the bat'leth in your hands. Describe the first thought that enters your mind.</td></tr>

<tr id="L68"><td><a href="#L68">68</a></td><td>TORRES:  It's a clumsy weapon. Overstated, like everything else Klingon.</td></tr>

<tr id="L69"><td><a href="#L69">69</a></td><td>TUVOK:  You can't see the elegance of its design because of your hatred.</td></tr>

<tr id="L70"><td><a href="#L70">70</a></td><td>TORRES:  I don't hate Klingons.</td></tr>

<tr id="L71"><td><a href="#L71">71</a></td><td>TUVOK:  It's a warrior's blade, crafted for precision and balance. Observe.</td></tr>

<tr id="L72"><td><a href="#L72">72</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Tuvok twirls the big blade around his body and head, ending up with the long curved edge inches from Torres' neck. The final set of fast moves end up cutting her cheek.</td></tr>

<tr id="L73"><td><a href="#L73">73</a></td><td>TORRES:  Is this your idea of therapy?</td></tr>

<tr id="L74"><td><a href="#L74">74</a></td><td>TUVOK:  Listen to yourself whine like a Ferengi.</td></tr>

<tr id="L75"><td><a href="#L75">75</a></td><td>TORRES:  PetaQ!</td></tr>

<tr id="L76"><td><a href="#L76">76</a></td><td>TUVOK:  You're not worthy of the blood in your veins. A true Klingon would try to kill me where I stand.</td></tr>

<tr id="L77"><td><a href="#L77">77</a></td><td>TORRES:  What the hell has gotten into you?</td></tr>

<tr id="L78"><td><a href="#L78">78</a></td><td>TUVOK:  This exercise is over. You are dismissed, Lieutenant, and take your dishonour with you.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Mess hall</td></tr>
<tr id="L79"><td><a href="#L79">79</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: The EMH is singing a Klingon song when Torres enters.</td></tr>

